[beta]
version=1.6.5.beta
downloadwin=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/1wlR0mQy
downloadmac=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/2WlR01RH
downloadlinux=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/Sylx0Sl4
changelog=
 <p><b>Changes from 1.6.4 to 1.6.5.beta</b></p>
 <p><i>Airspace view will be reset to default.</i></p>
 <ul>
   <li>Added OpenAir airspace format compilation for X-PLane. Reading &quot;*.txt&quot; files from
     &quot;YOURXPLANE/Custom Data/Airspaces&quot;,
     &quot;YOURXPLANE/Resources/default data/airspaces&quot; and
     from &quot;YOURHOME/Documents/Little Navmap/X-Plane Airspaces&quot; where &quot;Documents&quot; is the documents directory in you local language.</li>
   <li>Added scenery file display for airspaces in information window.</li>
   <li>Changed rating checkbox to combo in airport search.</li>
   <li>X-Plane 3D airport state now considered when calculating rating.</li>
   <li>Added display of simulator type to connection status in statusbar.</li>
   <li>Added display of AIRAC cycle to database dialog (only X-Plane).</li>
   <li>Enabled user defined waypoint names for X-Plane FMS format.</li>
   <li>Removed restrictions on user defined waypoint names. Names are now adjusted according to save flight plan format.</li>
   <li>Added coordinates to CSV export by clipboard.</li>
   <li>Added download button to update notification dialog.</li>
   <li>Fixed user waypoint format for FLP so that it can be reloaded.</li>
   <li>Fixed status bar connection indication remaining in disconnected state sometimes.</li>
   <li>Fixed &quot;Connect on startup&quot; checkbox state not saved in some cases.</li>
   <li>Solved problem with gaps between SIDs, STARs and the respective transitions resulting in wrong display and distance calculation.</li>
   <li>Fixed problem where STAR was not reloaded after database switch in some cases.</li>
   <li>Cleanup of airspace management code to allow addition of more airspace types (&quot;Wave Window&quot; and &quot;Glider Prohibited&quot;).</li>
   <li>Now clipping long airport and waypoint names on map.</li>
   <li>Fixed issue where airspaces were not updated when changing cruise altitude with empty flight plan.</li>
   <li>Fixed potential crash on failing network connection.</li>
   <li>Fixed problem loading certain FS9 flight plans.</li>
   <li>Fixed confusing 0 error dialog appearing after loading X-Plane database successfully.</li>
   <li>Now checking X-Plane CIFP filenames before loading. Wrong names are reported.</li>
   <li>Better error handling and reporting of too old files with version < 850 when loading X-Plane scenery.</li>
   <li>Added handler for assertions/crashes showing dialog to avoid crash to desktop.</li>
   <li>Made loading of add-on.xml more robust for files with wrong encoding.</li>
   <li>Increased database minor version to 3.</li>
   <li>Removed &quot;no SimConnect&quot; header label in connect dialog.</li>
   <li>Fixed several small text errors in GUI.</li>
 </ul>
 </small>

